{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":723,"text":"I'm 150 feet down an illegal mine shaft in Ghana."},{"time":7123,"text":"The air is thick with heat and dust,"},{"time":11244,"text":"and it's hard to breathe."},{"time":14653,"text":"I can feel the brush of sweaty bodies passing me"},{"time":17915,"text":"in the darkness, but I can't see much else."},{"time":22161,"text":"I hear voices talking, but mostly the shaft"},{"time":26131,"text":"is this cacophony of men coughing,"},{"time":30119,"text":"and stone being broken with primitive tools."},{"time":34030,"text":"Like the others, I wear a flickering, cheap flashlight"},{"time":38085,"text":"tied to my head with this elastic, tattered band,"},{"time":42881,"text":"and I can barely make out the slick tree limbs"},{"time":46221,"text":"holding up the walls of the three-foot square hole"},{"time":49250,"text":"dropping hundreds of feet into the earth."},{"time":53876,"text":"When my hand slips, I suddenly remember a miner"},{"time":56956,"text":"I had met days before who had lost his grip"},{"time":61237,"text":"and fell countless feet down that shaft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65858,"text":"As I stand talking to you today,"},{"time":68389,"text":"these men are still deep in that hole,"},{"time":71893,"text":"risking their lives without payment or compensation,"},{"time":75408,"text":"and often dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78548,"text":"I got to climb out of that hole, and I got to go home,"},{"time":83736,"text":"but they likely never will, because they're trapped in slavery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89918,"text":"For the last 28 years, I've been documenting"},{"time":92825,"text":"indigenous cultures in more than 70 countries"},{"time":95386,"text":"on six continents, and in 2009 I had the great honor"},{"time":99181,"text":"of being the sole exhibitor at the Vancouver Peace Summit."},{"time":103593,"text":"Amongst all the astonishing people I met there,"},{"time":107165,"text":"I met a supporter of Free the Slaves, an NGO"},{"time":110335,"text":"dedicated to eradicating modern day slavery."},{"time":115662,"text":"We started talking about slavery, and really,"},{"time":118551,"text":"I started learning about slavery,"},{"time":121415,"text":"for I had certainly known it existed in the world,"},{"time":124624,"text":"but not to such a degree."},{"time":127635,"text":"After we finished talking, I felt so horrible"},{"time":131378,"text":"and honestly ashamed at my own lack of knowledge"},{"time":134754,"text":"of this atrocity in my own lifetime, and I thought,"},{"time":138264,"text":"if I don't know, how many other people don't know?"},{"time":143132,"text":"It started burning a hole in my stomach, so within weeks,"},{"time":146947,"text":"I flew down to Los Angeles to meet with the director"},{"time":149923,"text":"of Free the Slaves and offer them my help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153194,"text":"Thus began my journey into modern day slavery."},{"time":157764,"text":"Oddly, I had been to many of these places before."},{"time":160906,"text":"Some I even considered like my second home."},{"time":164387,"text":"But this time, I would see the skeletons hidden in the closet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171822,"text":"A conservative estimate tells us there are more than"},{"time":174127,"text":"27 million people enslaved in the world today."},{"time":178282,"text":"That's double the amount of people taken from Africa"},{"time":181762,"text":"during the entire trans-Atlantic slave trade."},{"time":185887,"text":"A hundred and fifty years ago, an agricultural slave"},{"time":189031,"text":"cost about three times the annual salary"},{"time":192525,"text":"of an American worker."},{"time":195271,"text":"That equates to about $50,000 in today's money."},{"time":199264,"text":"Yet today, entire families can be enslaved for generations"},{"time":203656,"text":"over a debt as small as $18."},{"time":208524,"text":"Astonishingly, slavery generates profits"},{"time":211556,"text":"of more than $13 billion worldwide each year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217302,"text":"Many have been tricked by false promises"},{"time":220154,"text":"of a good education, a better job, only to find"},{"time":224700,"text":"that they're forced to work without pay"},{"time":228208,"text":"under the threat of violence, and they cannot walk away."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233876,"text":"Today's slavery is about commerce,"},{"time":237158,"text":"so the goods that enslaved people produce have value,"},{"time":241188,"text":"but the people producing them are disposable."},{"time":246186,"text":"Slavery exists everywhere, nearly, in the world,"},{"time":250576,"text":"and yet it is illegal everywhere in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257543,"text":"In India and Nepal, I was introduced to the brick kilns."},{"time":262333,"text":"This strange and awesome sight was like"},{"time":265124,"text":"walking into ancient Egypt or Dante's Inferno."},{"time":269014,"text":"Enveloped in temperatures of 130 degrees,"},{"time":273165,"text":"men, women, children, entire families in fact,"},{"time":277260,"text":"were cloaked in a heavy blanket of dust,"},{"time":280411,"text":"while mechanically stacking bricks on their head,"},{"time":283031,"text":"up to 18 at a time, and carrying them"},{"time":286152,"text":"from the scorching kilns to trucks hundreds of yards away."},{"time":291102,"text":"Deadened by monotony and exhaustion,"},{"time":294629,"text":"they work silently, doing this task over and over"},{"time":300214,"text":"for 16 or 17 hours a day."},{"time":303567,"text":"There were no breaks for food, no water breaks,"},{"time":307286,"text":"and the severe dehydration made urinating"},{"time":309838,"text":"pretty much inconsequential."},{"time":312710,"text":"So pervasive was the heat and the dust"},{"time":315142,"text":"that my camera became too hot to even touch"},{"time":318893,"text":"and ceased working."},{"time":321345,"text":"Every 20 minutes, I'd have to run back to our cruiser"},{"time":324117,"text":"to clean out my gear and run it under an air conditioner"},{"time":327466,"text":"to revive it, and as I sat there,"},{"time":330521,"text":"I thought, my camera is getting far better treatment"},{"time":335131,"text":"than these people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337457,"text":"Back in the kilns, I wanted to cry,"},{"time":340329,"text":"but the abolitionist next to me quickly grabbed me"},{"time":343507,"text":"and he said, \"Lisa, don't do that. Just don't do that here.\""},{"time":347811,"text":"And he very clearly explained to me that emotional displays"},{"time":351704,"text":"are very dangerous in a place like this,"},{"time":354238,"text":"not just for me, but for them."},{"time":358092,"text":"I couldn't offer them any direct help."},{"time":361742,"text":"I couldn't give them money, nothing."},{"time":364535,"text":"I wasn't a citizen of that country."},{"time":366332,"text":"I could get them in a worse situation"},{"time":369420,"text":"than they were already in."},{"time":372200,"text":"I'd have to rely on Free the Slaves to work"},{"time":374456,"text":"within the system for their liberation,"},{"time":377298,"text":"and I trusted that they would."},{"time":380767,"text":"As for me, I'd have to wait until I got home"},{"time":384204,"text":"to really feel my heartbreak."}]},{"cues":[{"time":388166,"text":"In the Himalayas, I found children carrying stone"},{"time":391039,"text":"for miles down mountainous terrain"},{"time":393789,"text":"to trucks waiting at roads below."},{"time":396687,"text":"The big sheets of slate were heavier"},{"time":399205,"text":"than the children carrying them,"},{"time":401871,"text":"and the kids hoisted them from their heads"},{"time":403900,"text":"using these handmade harnesses of sticks and rope"},{"time":408344,"text":"and torn cloth."},{"time":410191,"text":"It's difficult to witness something so overwhelming."},{"time":413866,"text":"How can we affect something so insidious,"},{"time":416513,"text":"yet so pervasive?"},{"time":419725,"text":"Some don't even know they're enslaved,"},{"time":422437,"text":"people working 16, 17 hours a day without any pay,"},{"time":427443,"text":"because this has been the case all their lives."},{"time":430656,"text":"They have nothing to compare it to."},{"time":434938,"text":"When these villagers claimed their freedom,"},{"time":438312,"text":"the slaveholders burned down all of their houses."},{"time":443727,"text":"I mean, these people had nothing,"},{"time":445689,"text":"and they were so petrified, they wanted to give up,"},{"time":449338,"text":"but the woman in the center rallied for them to persevere,"},{"time":453385,"text":"and abolitionists on the ground"},{"time":454881,"text":"helped them get a quarry lease of their own,"},{"time":457540,"text":"so that now they do the same back-breaking work,"},{"time":460653,"text":"but they do it for themselves, and they get paid for it,"},{"time":465160,"text":"and they do it in freedom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468583,"text":"Sex trafficking is what we often think of"},{"time":470651,"text":"when we hear the word slavery,"},{"time":472552,"text":"and because of this worldwide awareness,"},{"time":474511,"text":"I was warned that it would be difficult for me to work safely"},{"time":477647,"text":"within this particular industry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480469,"text":"In Kathmandu, I was escorted by women who had"},{"time":483311,"text":"previously been sex slaves themselves."},{"time":486847,"text":"They ushered me down a narrow set of stairs"},{"time":489205,"text":"that led to this dirty, dimly fluorescent lit basement."},{"time":494818,"text":"This wasn't a brothel, per se."},{"time":496650,"text":"It was more like a restaurant."},{"time":498961,"text":"Cabin restaurants, as they're known in the trade,"},{"time":501221,"text":"are venues for forced prostitution."},{"time":503843,"text":"Each has small, private rooms, where the slaves,"},{"time":506875,"text":"women, along with young girls and boys,"},{"time":509506,"text":"some as young as seven years old,"},{"time":512285,"text":"are forced to entertain the clients,"},{"time":514275,"text":"encouraging them to buy more food and alcohol."},{"time":518055,"text":"Each cubicle is dark and dingy,"},{"time":521094,"text":"identified with a painted number on the wall,"},{"time":525033,"text":"and partitioned by plywood and a curtain."},{"time":529138,"text":"The workers here often endure tragic sexual abuse"},{"time":532689,"text":"at the hands of their customers."},{"time":535271,"text":"Standing in the near darkness, I remember feeling"},{"time":538337,"text":"this quick, hot fear, and in that instant,"},{"time":542423,"text":"I could only imagine what it must be like"},{"time":544768,"text":"to be trapped in that hell."},{"time":547431,"text":"I had only one way out: the stairs from where I'd come in."},{"time":552033,"text":"There were no back doors."},{"time":553889,"text":"There were no windows large enough to climb through."},{"time":556432,"text":"These people have no escape at all,"},{"time":560692,"text":"and as we take in such a difficult subject,"},{"time":563752,"text":"it's important to note that slavery, including sex trafficking,"},{"time":568363,"text":"occurs in our own backyard as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571292,"text":"Tens of hundreds of people are enslaved in agriculture,"},{"time":575916,"text":"in restaurants, in domestic servitude,"},{"time":578588,"text":"and the list can go on."},{"time":581220,"text":"Recently, the New York Times reported that"},{"time":583859,"text":"between 100,000 and 300,000 American children"},{"time":589665,"text":"are sold into sex slavery every year."},{"time":593626,"text":"It's all around us. We just don't see it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600169,"text":"The textile industry is another one we often think of"},{"time":603551,"text":"when we hear about slave labor."},{"time":606437,"text":"I visited villages in India where entire families were enslaved"},{"time":610760,"text":"in the silk trade."},{"time":613405,"text":"This is a family portrait."},{"time":615697,"text":"The dyed black hands are the father, while the blue"},{"time":619585,"text":"and red hands are his sons."},{"time":622374,"text":"They mix dye in these big barrels,"},{"time":625098,"text":"and they submerge the silk into the liquid up to their elbows,"},{"time":629063,"text":"but the dye is toxic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":634025,"text":"My interpreter told me their stories."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637330,"text":"\"We have no freedom,\" they said."},{"time":640932,"text":"\"We hope still, though, that we could leave this house"},{"time":644036,"text":"someday and go someplace else"},{"time":645690,"text":"where we actually get paid for our dyeing.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":652354,"text":"It's estimated that more than 4,000 children"},{"time":657293,"text":"are enslaved on Lake Volta,"},{"time":659450,"text":"the largest man-made lake in the world."},{"time":663536,"text":"When we first arrived, I went to have a quick look."},{"time":666510,"text":"I saw what seemed to be a family fishing on a boat,"},{"time":669878,"text":"two older brothers, some younger kids, makes sense right?"},{"time":674043,"text":"Wrong. They were all enslaved."},{"time":678091,"text":"Children are taken from their families"},{"time":680920,"text":"and trafficked and vanished,"},{"time":683427,"text":"and they're forced to work endless hours on these boats"},{"time":686339,"text":"on the lake, even though they do not know how to swim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690886,"text":"This young child is eight years old."},{"time":693221,"text":"He was trembling when our boat approached,"},{"time":695877,"text":"frightened it would run over his tiny canoe."},{"time":698532,"text":"He was petrified he would be knocked in the water."},{"time":701871,"text":"The skeletal tree limbs submerged in Lake Volta"},{"time":705156,"text":"often catch the fishing nets, and weary,"},{"time":709121,"text":"frightened children are thrown into the water"},{"time":712854,"text":"to untether the lines."},{"time":715005,"text":"Many of them drown."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717852,"text":"For as long as he can recall, he's been forced to work"},{"time":721192,"text":"on the lake."},{"time":723365,"text":"Terrified of his master, he will not run away,"},{"time":726829,"text":"and since he's been treated with cruelty all his life,"},{"time":730317,"text":"he passes that down to the younger slaves"},{"time":732749,"text":"that he manages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735754,"text":"I met these boys at five in the morning,"},{"time":737858,"text":"when they were hauling in the last of their nets,"},{"time":740319,"text":"but they had been working since 1 a.m."},{"time":743180,"text":"in the cold, windy night."},{"time":746755,"text":"And it's important to note that these nets weigh"},{"time":750021,"text":"more than a thousand pounds when they're full of fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754437,"text":"I want to introduce you to Kofi."},{"time":758940,"text":"Kofi was rescued from a fishing village."},{"time":762186,"text":"I met him at a shelter where Free the Slaves"},{"time":764778,"text":"rehabilitates victims of slavery."},{"time":768707,"text":"Here he's seen taking a bath at the well,"},{"time":770788,"text":"pouring big buckets of water over his head,"},{"time":773691,"text":"and the wonderful news is,"},{"time":775612,"text":"as you and I are sitting here talking today,"},{"time":777610,"text":"Kofi has been reunited with his family,"},{"time":780845,"text":"and what's even better, his family has been given tools"},{"time":783997,"text":"to make a living and to keep their children safe."},{"time":789724,"text":"Kofi is the embodiment of possibility."},{"time":794177,"text":"Who will he become because someone took a stand"},{"time":798748,"text":"and made a difference in his life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":802340,"text":"Driving down a road in Ghana"},{"time":804568,"text":"with partners of Free the Slaves,"},{"time":806656,"text":"a fellow abolitionist on a moped suddenly sped up"},{"time":809698,"text":"to our cruiser and tapped on the window."},{"time":812645,"text":"He told us to follow him down a dirt road into the jungle."},{"time":817425,"text":"At the end of the road, he urged us out of the car,"},{"time":820214,"text":"and told the driver to quickly leave."},{"time":822893,"text":"Then he pointed toward this barely visible footpath,"},{"time":826238,"text":"and said, \"This is the path, this is the path. Go.\""},{"time":830135,"text":"As we started down the path, we pushed aside the vines"},{"time":833804,"text":"blocking the way, and after about an hour of walking in,"},{"time":837604,"text":"found that the trail had become flooded by recent rains,"},{"time":843130,"text":"so I hoisted the photo gear above my head"},{"time":844946,"text":"as we descended into these waters up to my chest."},{"time":849532,"text":"After another two hours of hiking, the winding trail"},{"time":853317,"text":"abruptly ended at a clearing, and before us"},{"time":857613,"text":"was a mass of holes"},{"time":859629,"text":"that could fit into the size of a football field,"},{"time":863449,"text":"and all of them were full of enslaved people laboring."},{"time":869043,"text":"Many women had children strapped to their backs"},{"time":872188,"text":"while they were panning for gold,"},{"time":874228,"text":"wading in water poisoned by mercury."},{"time":878531,"text":"Mercury is used in the extraction process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883409,"text":"These miners are enslaved in a mine shaft"},{"time":886565,"text":"in another part of Ghana."},{"time":889639,"text":"When they came out of the shaft, they were soaking wet"},{"time":892460,"text":"from their own sweat."},{"time":894738,"text":"I remember looking into their tired, bloodshot eyes,"},{"time":898741,"text":"for many of them had been underground for 72 hours."},{"time":904482,"text":"The shafts are up to 300 feet deep, and they carry out"},{"time":908457,"text":"heavy bags of stone that later will be transported"},{"time":912026,"text":"to another area, where the stone will be pounded"},{"time":914627,"text":"so that they can extract the gold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918572,"text":"At first glance, the pounding site seems full"},{"time":922677,"text":"of powerful men, but when we look closer,"},{"time":927570,"text":"we see some less fortunate working on the fringes,"},{"time":932437,"text":"and children too."},{"time":934580,"text":"All of them are victim to injury, illness and violence."},{"time":941722,"text":"In fact, it's very likely that this muscular person"},{"time":945702,"text":"will end up like this one here, racked with tuberculosis"},{"time":950237,"text":"and mercury poisoning in just a few years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955208,"text":"This is Manuru. When his father died,"},{"time":959485,"text":"his uncle trafficked him to work with him in the mines."},{"time":962567,"text":"When his uncle died, Manuru inherited his uncle's debt,"},{"time":967163,"text":"which further forced him into being enslaved in the mines."},{"time":972105,"text":"When I met him, he had been working in the mines"},{"time":974938,"text":"for 14 years, and the leg injury that you see here"},{"time":979731,"text":"is actually from a mining accident,"},{"time":981744,"text":"one so severe doctors say his leg should be amputated."},{"time":986877,"text":"On top of that, Manuru has tuberculosis,"},{"time":990827,"text":"yet he's still forced to work day in and day out"},{"time":993871,"text":"in that mine shaft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996115,"text":"Even still, he has a dream that he will become free"},{"time":1001278,"text":"and become educated with the help of local activists"},{"time":1004391,"text":"like Free the Slaves,"},{"time":1006819,"text":"and it's this sort of determination,"},{"time":1009171,"text":"in the face of unimaginable odds,"},{"time":1013049,"text":"that fills me with complete awe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020409,"text":"I want to shine a light on slavery."},{"time":1023709,"text":"When I was working in the field,"},{"time":1025964,"text":"I brought lots of candles with me,"},{"time":1028645,"text":"and with the help of my interpreter,"},{"time":1031367,"text":"I imparted to the people I was photographing"},{"time":1033683,"text":"that I wanted to illuminate their stories"},{"time":1036794,"text":"and their plight,"},{"time":1038861,"text":"so when it was safe for them, and safe for me,"},{"time":1042366,"text":"I made these images."},{"time":1045707,"text":"They knew their image would be seen"},{"time":1047940,"text":"by you out in the world."},{"time":1049769,"text":"I wanted them to know that we will be bearing witness"},{"time":1053513,"text":"to them, and that we will do whatever we can"},{"time":1057442,"text":"to help make a difference in their lives."},{"time":1062132,"text":"I truly believe, if we can see one another"},{"time":1065612,"text":"as fellow human beings, then it becomes very difficult"},{"time":1070096,"text":"to tolerate atrocities like slavery."},{"time":1075300,"text":"These images are not of issues. They are of people,"},{"time":1078984,"text":"real people, like you and me, all deserving"},{"time":1082249,"text":"of the same rights, dignity and respect"},{"time":1085729,"text":"in their lives."},{"time":1087958,"text":"There is not a day that goes by that I don't think"},{"time":1091193,"text":"of these many beautiful, mistreated people"},{"time":1096472,"text":"I've had the tremendous honor of meeting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101041,"text":"I hope that these images awaken a force"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1104571,"text":"in those who view them, people like you,"},{"time":1107617,"text":"and I hope that force will ignite a fire,"},{"time":1111893,"text":"and that fire will shine a light on slavery,"},{"time":1116816,"text":"for without that light, the beast of bondage"},{"time":1120825,"text":"can continue to live in the shadows."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1124009,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1126986,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}